The Mighty Doaug
	Create a village with a statue of the local god Doaug
		The statue has an engraving written in draconic
		The engraving is a misspelled version of 
			"I will bark at them loudly and quickly and they will kneel before the Mighty Doaug. 
			 I will howl every night so that they know they are under my paw... or tooth? or claw?"
		No one in the village can read draconic, but they wish to decipher the question that "Plagues the Mighty Doaug"
		The villagers believe that finding the answer to the question will cause Doaug to return and protect them
	Doaug is a half-dragon (blue) riding dog who fancies himself an honorable warrior
		Doaug refers to himself as The Mighty Doaug
		Doaug became a lesser god after conquering 5 settlements through intimidation alone, which Kyranious rewarded
		Doaug is the god of Conquest and Honorable Combat
		Doaug has the domains War and Strength
		Doaug can write broken draconic, but he can't read
		The reason the question plagues Doaug is because he can't remember it for long enough to answer it
	Doaug is currently looking for people to help him fight a 9-headed hydra
		Doaug believes the hydra to have cheated by regrowing its severed heads
		Doaug believes that he requires the tools of man to kill the beast
		Doaug doesn't remember why he first attacked the hydra